## ui_primitive_consolidation

### Current Progress
- **Phase 1: Primitive Components** — ✅ Complete
- **Phase 2: Input & Control Standardization** — ✅ Complete
- **Phase 3: Route & Layout Consolidation** — ✅ Builder/editor target slice complete
- **Phase 4: Design Token Hardening** — 🔄 Started

### Next Steps
- [x] 2026-06-09: `DerivedSectionBlock` and `CustomSectionBlock` now share the registered component picker/bind mapper path used by datasource previews.
- [x] 2026-06-17: Continued Phase 3 builder/editor standardization.
  - `DataSourceEditorPage` now uses `Button`/`Select` for editor topbar actions, cache selector, result tabs, component registry tab, save-section controls, and save-section dialog actions.
  - `PageBuilder` admin toolbar, landing dropdown, more-menu actions, engagement like/analytics controls, and visibility selector now use `Button`/`Select`.
  - `CardDesigner` now uses `Button` for reset/accordion/toggle/zone controls, `Select` for compact dropdowns, and `Tile` for card style choices.
  - `ColumnMapper` and `ComponentBindMapper` now use `Select` and `Button`; component bind inline styles moved to `ColumnMapper.css`.
  - `Button` primitive now renders plain children directly unless icon/loading slots require the label wrapper, preserving complex custom button layouts.
- [x] 2026-06-17: Started Phase 4 token hardening for touched surfaces.
  - Moved static DataSource component picker/preview styles, fetch chevron color, skipped-count color, PageBuilder empty/error state styles, PageBuilder reset danger color, and CardDesigner radius-row sizing out of JSX into CSS.
  - Targeted grep confirms no raw `<button>`, `<select>`, or checkbox controls remain in `DataSourceEditorPage`, `PageBuilder`, `CardDesigner`, `ColumnMapper`, or `ComponentBindMapper`.
  - Targeted grep confirms no `.btn-custom`, `.select-box`, `.cd-ctrl select`, or `.column-mapper-slot-value select` legacy selectors remain in the touched CSS paths.
  - Verification: `mise exec node@24.16.0 -- npm run build` passes (`tsc -b && vite build`); Vite reports existing large chunk warnings only.
- [x] 2026-06-17: Correctness/auditor diff follow-up fixed a visual regression in the initial migration.
  - Finding: migrated custom-class buttons were rendered through `Button` without preserving visual ownership, so the primitive default `primary` styling could alter compact/action/source button appearances.
  - Fix: added `unstyled` support to `Button` and applied it to migrated custom-class button call sites in the touched datasource/page-builder/card-designer/mapper surfaces.
  - Verification: targeted PCRE2 grep confirms no migrated custom-class `Button` in the touched files lacks `unstyled`; `mise exec node@24.16.0 -- npm run build` passes.
- [x] 2026-06-17: Correctness/auditor pass unified the custom page-builder datasource/component picker controls.
  - Finding: `ComponentGroupEditor`, `DerivedSectionBlock`, `CustomSectionBlock`, and `DataSourcesBlock` were still duplicating raw button/select controls around the registered component picker and datasource/custom-section selection paths.
  - Fix: migrated `ComponentGroupEditor` tabs/add/remove/component select to `Button`/`Select`; migrated derived/custom section datasource/custom-section, row-key, and component selectors to `Select`; migrated refresh and datasource-management actions to `Button` with `unstyled` where existing class CSS owns visuals.
  - CSS bridge updates now target `.sk-select__native` for component group, derived section, and custom section controls, with explicit right padding and `background-image: none` to avoid duplicate arrows.
  - Verification: targeted grep confirms no raw `<button>`, `<select>`, or checkbox controls remain in `ComponentGroupEditor`, `DerivedSectionBlock`, `CustomSectionBlock`, or `DataSourcesBlock`; `mise exec node@24.16.0 -- npm run build` passes.
- [x] 2026-06-17: Migrated section animation controls in `EditControls`.
  - `SectionAnimationControl` now uses `Select` for animation style and `Button unstyled` for compact intensity buttons.
  - `page-builder-core.css` now styles `.section-animation-control .sk-select__native` with explicit padding and `background-image: none`.
  - Verification: `mise exec node@24.16.0 -- npm run build` passes.
- [ ] Continue Phase 4: Broaden token/inline-style audit beyond the touched builder/editor files, including global `index.css` checkbox rules and remaining page-builder/layout block inline styles.

